Lackit being now in caſh, was in hopes to take Ramble in for another fifty at the hazard-table; but Ramble,

whoſe thoughts were wholly on Miſs Raſpe, begged to be excuſed joining his party that day and took his leave, ſaying to himſelf, when alone, He has probably humbugged me;
                   yet conſoled himſelf with obſerving, that too often with the over-cautious has a fear of being over-reached or deceived, prevented their doing many a good and generous action.
